---
title: Puglia-Style Roasted Tomato Orecchiette with Parmesan & Parsley
description: This simple, rustic pasta dish will take you straight to the heel of Italy’s boot–the Puglia region, where this dish is from. It stars burst tomatoes roasted with garlic and panko and a glossy olive-oil rich sauce. You’ll garnish it generously with Parmesan and parsley and there it is–an authentic Italian dinner in a quick 20 minutes–delizioso!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/664362e638584bf020f8c6b1-78efb006.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/664362e638584bf020f8c6b1-en-US.pdf
cuisine: Southern Europe
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/puglia-style-roasted-tomato-orecchiette-664362e638584bf020f8c6b1
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
time required: 20 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 720 kcal
  fat: 34 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 82 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 21 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 240 mg
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of @salt{} water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and finely dice @onion{1}(peeled and finely diced). Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}(minced or grated). Roughly chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}(roughly chopped).

Toss @grape tomatoes{8%ounces}, onion, garlic, and @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} on a #baking sheet{} with @cooking oil{2%teaspoons}, @dried oregano{1%teaspoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until tomatoes burst, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Once water is boiling, add @orecchiette pasta{6%ounces} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Drain.

Return drained orecchiette to pot. Drizzle with @olive oil{3%tablespoons}.

Add roasted tomato mixture to pot with pasta; stir to combine, adding more olive oil a drizzle at a time if needed, until everything is coated in a glossy sauce.

> Stir pasta vigorously to prevent it from sticking together.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide pasta between shallow #bowls{}. Garnish with @parmesan cheese{6%tablespoons} and parsley. Serve.